Science Hack day, Nairobi 2012 - Large Hadron collider data hack. Visualizations with matplotlib and Basemap.  

################################################################################
# For Matt's code
################################################################################

Make sure you have 
python, numpy, matplotlib, and basemap installed.

Create a directory here called 'frames'. Then run

  python make_map_images_bellis.py

This will create a bunch of single frames that can be joined together to make
a movie. The file cmds.sh has some commands to convert these. For instance,

  ffmpeg -r 25 -qscale 2 -i frames/movie_frames_%04d.png two_muons.mp4


